36yo, P1 - previous SVD, 1 day postnatal review, BMI 24, Rh+ve.
- Patient recovering well post-delivery, mobilizing, and managing pain with paracetamol and ibuprofen.
- Requested laxatives due to anxiety about passing stool.
- Baby boy Jesse feeding and sleeping well, with minor redness under left eye.
- No concerning signs of complications like hematoma or hemorrhage.
- Reassuring clinical picture for both mother and baby.
- Plan for discharge tomorrow pending continued progress.
- Follow-up with birth stories team recommended.
- Text submitted for review of delivery process and instruments used.
